0. Create project using Maven
--> File - New Maven Project - Maven Archetype(template) Web App
                             - Project Structure for Web App

jsp --> java server page(fe, java, jsp syntax)
                             
1. Fix error after create project
   + Structure
   		src
   			main
   				java(src/main/java)           --> Backend: code & configuration(bye java)
   				resources(src/main/resources) --> Backend: code & resources(.properties)
   				webapp                        --> Frontend: code
   					WEB-INF(configure)
   						web.xml(main-config with xml)
   					index.jsp(first come when start application)
   					
   + index.jsp(error first)
   	 --> The superclass "javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet" was not found on the Java Build Path
	 --> java extends/implement HttpServlet
	 	 --> import dependency for servlet/jsp(contains HttpServlet)
	 	 

2. Import dependencies for web
   spring-webmvc
   	 core, aop, context, web(dependencies)

3. Configure DispatcherServlet || FrontController
   --> manage request mapping/functions existed in webapp
   --> web browser --> front controller -- (OK)   -- webapp function
   										-- (FAIL) -- return web browser with error
   + XML  : web.xml
   + JAVA : .......
   ==> Configure necessary parameters for Spring MVC Application
      + spring-mvc-config.xml

4. Controller
   + index.jsp
   + request mapping/function
     --> default(empty or /) --> WEB-INF/view/hompage.jsp
   
5.1 View Resolver
	Class --> prefix = /WEB-INF/view/
		      suffix = .jsp
	
	return homepage       --> prefix+homepage+suffix --> /WEB-INF/view/homepage.jsp
	return student/index  /WEB-INF/view/student/index.jsp

5.2 View Template
   jsp(fe, java, jsp syntax) --> convert html to show in web browser
   return /WEB-INF/view/homepage.jsp

